    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>and <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p><p>Once the vegetables have softened, add your <strong>drained green lentils</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>creamy single soy</strong> to the pan and bring to a boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 10-12 min, stirring regularly, until the sauce has thickened to a risotto-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>plant-based tomato green lentil risotto</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> panko breadcrumbs </strong>and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until golden, stirring frequently</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Once golden, add the <strong>chopped parsley</strong> to the breadcrumbs<strong> </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>herby garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/plant-based-tomato-green-lentil-risotto/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>plant-based tomato green lentil risotto </strong>topped with the <strong>herby garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Serve the <strong>salad</strong> to the side and drizzle over your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
